}],["design",{"_index":20,"t":{"1410":{"position":[[49,8]]},"1412":{"position":[[13,8]]}}}],["desktop",{"_index":26,"t":{"1412":{"position":[[61,7]]}}}],["driven",{"_index":13,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[38,6]]}}}],["interact",{"_index":25,"t":{"1412":{"position":[[49,11]]}}}],["licens",{"_index":22,"t":{"1412":{"position":[[22,8]]}}}],["mainten",{"_index":4,"t":{"1398":{"position":[[32,11]]}}}],["manual",{"_index":21,"t":{"1410":{"position":[[58,7]]}}}],["note",{"_index":1,"t":{"1398":{"position":[[8,5]]}}}],["page",{"_index":9,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[5,4]]}}}],["placehold",{"_index":17,"t":{"1410":{"position":[[8,11]]}}}],["prototyp",{"_index":10,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[10,10]]}}}],["refer",{"_index":14,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[45,9]]}}}],["releas",{"_index":0,"t":{"1398":{"position":[[0,7]]}}}],["rfc'",{"_index":11,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[25,5]]}}}],["schema",{"_index":12,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[31,6]]}}}],["short",{"_index":16,"t":{"1410":{"position":[[2,5]]}}}],["stad",{"_index":24,"t":{"1412":{"position":[[36,5]]}}}],["sttar",{"_index":2,"t":{"1398":{"position":[[22,5]]}}}],["tabl",{"_index":15,"t":{"1406":{"position":[[55,7],[67,5]]}}}],["walkthrough",{"_index":18,"t":{"1410":{"position":[[20,11]]}}}]],"pipeline":["stemmer"]}},{"documents":[],"index":{"version":"2.3.9","fields":["t"],"fieldVectors":[],"invertedIndex":[],"pipeline":["stemmer"]}},{"documents":[{"i":1399,"t":"Release notes for the STTAR 2.3 maintenance branch (2.3.0 → 2.3.15). The 2.3 line has been a long-running maintenance branch, accumulating a steady stream of fixes and small improvements over four years (2.3.0 through 2.3.15). Below is a consolidated digest of the most user-visible changes.","s":"What changed in this version","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/changelog","h":"","p":1398},{"i":1401,"t":"New — Net_Cabinets and Net_PathwayAccessStructures map layers (2.3.13.5739) Cabinets and pathway access structures are now exposed as dedicated map layers. New — Cloud server support (2.3.14.5770) A new Sttarcloud build configuration plus a --cloudlicensemaxendpoints command-line option enable Sttar to run in cloud-server scenarios with endpoint-count licensing. New — --inputdir CLI argument (2.3.12.5707) A new optional argument lets users specify a different base directory for data sources when opening an SDCONFIG file.","s":"Highlights","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/changelog","h":"#highlights","p":1398},{"i":1403,"t":"Improved — CablingDiagram — conduit variables (2.3.13.5739) New variables related to conduits have been added to the CablingDiagram report. Improved — Map context-menu — multi-conduit details (2.3.13.5739) The conduit identifier and model number are now displayed in the map context menu when several conduits or sections are selected. Improved — Google Street View provider refresh (2.3.13.5739) The integrated Street View panoramic provider has been updated following the end of support for older Internet browsers. Improved — Splice-plan splitter usage (2.3.13.5739) When the last splitter of a given ratio is not full and smaller split-ratios are available, the plan now optimises usage across them.","s":"Improvements","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/changelog","h":"#improvements","p":1398},{"i":1405,"t":"Fixed — Routing & splice plan (2.3.12.5707, 2.3.13.5739) Splice plan failure when several splitters are on the same upstream fibre; collocated endpoints incorrectly removed from the routing graph in Advanced Search; passthrough mistakenly reusing fibres allocated to a splitter; connecting support of nodes collocated with multiple infrastructures. Fixed — Export and reports (2.3.13.5739, 2.3.14.5770, 2.3.15.5798) Esri FileGDB and AutoCAD DXF export failures; Link Budget export issue; RemoveMultiPartGeometries filter generating straight-line polylines incorrectly; Net_PathwayAccessStructure not removed from the map legend when the network design is cleared. Fixed — Stability (2.3.13.5739, 2.3.14.5770, 2.3.15.5798) Infinite loop in the JoinLineStringsBetweenJunctions filter under certain conditions; Duct Settings view failing to open on projects with invalid Support references; Euro currency English label corrected from \"Croatian Kuna\" to \"Euro\".","s":"Bug fixes","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/changelog","h":"#bug-fixes","p":1398},{"i":1407,"t":"This page prototypes the RFC's schema-driven reference tables: the table below is rendered from a JSON artifact (/sample-datamodel.json) that, in production, would be emitted by the STTAR build per version — so the reference always matches the code. Note The JSON is fetched at runtime from the static bundle. In production this artifact is versioned alongside the docs so each release shows its own schema.","s":"Data model reference","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/data-model","h":"","p":1406},{"i":1409,"t":"Loading schema… Warning Renaming a serialized field breaks old .sdconfig projects — see the STTAR compatibility adapters before changing the model.","s":"Support object","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/data-model","h":"#support-object","p":1406},{"i":1411,"t":"A short placeholder walkthrough for the Advanced Designer manual. Create a project. Import a support layer. Run the network optimizer. This page is intentionally thin — the draft validates plumbing, not content.","s":"Getting started","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/getting-started","h":"","p":1410},{"i":1413,"t":"The Advanced Designer (license code STAD) is the interactive desktop workspace for fiber-optic network design and optimization. This is placeholder content for the documentation-platform validation draft. It exists to prove the architecture (multi-manual, versioning, i18n, access gating, search) works end to end — not to document the product.","s":"Advanced Designer","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/intro","h":"","p":1412},{"i":1415,"t":"Project and network model concepts The optimization pipeline The data model reference (see Data Model) Use the version picker in the navbar to switch between documented STTAR releases. Each version has its own What changed page.","s":"What this manual covers","u":"/sttar-docs/advanced-designer/2.3/intro","h":"#what-this-manual-covers","p":1412}],"index":{"version":"2.3.9","fields":["t"],"fieldVectors":[["t/1399",[0,1.18,1,1.559,2,0.672,3,2.823,4,2.823,5,2.823,6,2.823,7,0.183,8,2.823,9,1.18,10,2.133,11,1.18,12,2.133,13,2.133,14,2.133,15,1.559,16,2.133,17,1.559,18,2.133,19,2.133,20,2.133,21,2.133,22,1.559,23,2.133,24,2.133,25,1.559,26,2.133,27,1.18]],["t/1401",[2,0.527,7,0.239,9,0.926,11,0.926,25,1.223,28,2.348,29,1.673,30,1.223,31,1.322,32,1.746,33,0.926,34,1.673,35,1.673,36,1.223,37,1.673,38,1.223,39,1.673,40,1.673,41,2.389,42,2.389,43,0.704,44,1.223,45,1.673,46,1.223,47,1.673,48,1.673,49,1.673,50,1.673,51,2.389,52,1.673,53,1.673,54,1.223,55,1.673,56,1.223,57,1.673,58,1.673,59,2.389,60,1.223,61,1.673,62,1.673,63,1.673,64,1.673,65,1.673,66,1.223,67,1.673,68,1.223,69,1.223,70,1.673]],["t/1403",[7,0.274,17,2.092,28,1.077,31,1.205,33,1.584,38,1.592,43,0.62,71,2.178,72,3.054,73,2.178,74,1.474,75,1.474,76,1.077,77,2.178,78,2.178,79,1.077,80,1.474,81,1.474,82,0.815,83,1.474,84,1.474,85,1.077,86,1.474,87,1.474,88,1.474,89,2.178,90,1.592,91,2.178,92,1.474,93,1.474,94,1.474,95,1.474,96,1.474,97,1.077,98,1.474,99,1.474,100,1.474,101,1.077,102,1.592,103,1.592,104,2.178,105,1.474,106,1.474,107,2.178,108,1.474,109,1.474,110,1.474,111,1.474,112,1.474]],["t/1405",[7,0.23,9,0.715,15,1.749,30,0.944,31,0.715,33,1.325,43,0.831,44,1.442,54,0.944,60,0.944,68,0.944,76,0.944,85,0.944,90,0.944,101,1.442,102,1.442,103,1.442,113,1.973,114,1.973,115,1.292,116,1.292,117,1.973,118,1.973,119,1.973,120,1.973,121,1.292,122,0.715,123,0.944,124,1.292,125,1.292,126,1.292,127,1.292,128,1.292,129,1.292,130,1.292,131,1.292,132,2.394,133,1.973,134,1.292,135,1.292,136,1.292,137,1.292,138,1.292,139,1.292,140,1.292,141,1.292,142,1.973,143,1.292,144,1.292,145,1.292,146,1.292,147,0.544,148,0.715,149,1.